reviewText: This was a surprisingly entertaining production throughout.  The characters were played well, casting seemed right and the story lines were not so completely convoluted that you got too lost along the way. Too bad they ran out of story lines but the ending was left at a comfortable stopping point.

It is impossible to give Perabo and her co-stars, writers, producers and directors too much praise for this series.  It is thoughtful, thought-provoking, and as close to an honest look at the world of a young person entering the CIA as I've ever seen.  With its extreme production values--on location shooting, attention to the details of foreign locales, customs, and honestly amazing casting even for minor characters--you cannot go wrong with buying this entire series.  As I may have said before, this series is like watching a 75 (seventy five!) hour (HOUR) movie that is still too short.  A career accomplishment for the entire crew to be proud of.
It was a great series, but I was wanting for more when it was over.
Great show wish it had not been canceled
